653
01:02:40,923 --> 01:02:43,619
I don't know.

654
01:02:43,693 --> 01:02:47,459
A couple of days, maybe three.

655
01:02:47,530 --> 01:02:49,464
Depends how long it takes.

656
01:02:50,767 --> 01:02:54,396
What number will you be at?
I haven't decided
who I'm gonna stay with yet.

657
01:02:54,470 --> 01:02:56,904
I think people are getting pretty sick
of me sleeping on their floors.

658
01:02:56,973 --> 01:03:00,409
So, I'll probably just
check into a bed-and-breakfast.

659
01:03:06,482 --> 01:03:09,451
You don't have to go,
you know.

660
01:03:13,890 --> 01:03:16,188
Yes, I do.

661
01:07:13,896 --> 01:07:15,887
Sylvia?

662
01:07:44,427 --> 01:07:46,588
The truth comes to me.

663
01:07:50,066 --> 01:07:52,694
The truth loves me.

664
01:08:08,451 --> 01:08:10,442
Hello?

665
01:08:13,089 --> 01:08:15,523
I know who you are.

666
01:08:21,230 --> 01:08:23,221
Hello.

667
01:08:35,144 --> 01:08:37,578
Get out.

668
01:10:54,917 --> 01:10:57,249
This is the light of the mind.

669
01:11:06,595 --> 01:11:10,588
If the moon smiled,
she would resemble you.
Their redness talks to my wound.

670
01:11:10,666 --> 01:11:13,692
She would drag me, cruelly,
being barren.

671
01:11:13,769 --> 01:11:16,260
Thick, red and slipping--

672
01:11:16,338 --> 01:11:19,330
Your nakedness shadows our safety.

673
01:11:21,110 --> 01:11:23,237
Whose is that long white box
on the grove?

674
01:11:23,312 --> 01:11:27,612
They can die, I need feed them nothing.

675
01:11:27,683 --> 01:11:29,617
I sizzled in his blue--

676
01:11:29,685 --> 01:11:32,677
Our cheesecloth gauntlets
neat and sweet--

677
01:11:32,755 --> 01:11:38,660
Bare-handed I hand the combs.
The man in white smiles--

678
01:11:38,727 --> 01:11:42,458
So I can't see what is in there.
Some god got hold of me--

679
01:11:42,531 --> 01:11:46,399
Lightly, through their white swaddlings,
like an awful baby--

680
01:11:46,468 --> 01:11:50,165
A world of bald white days
in a shadeless socket.

681
01:11:50,239 --> 01:11:53,640
I cannot undo myself,
and the train is steaming--

682
