Christmas is bloody hard.

737
01:16:21,643 --> 01:16:25,443
Can we-- Can we talk?
Can we sit down?

738
01:16:41,396 --> 01:16:43,557
Are you still fucking her?

739
01:17:13,528 --> 01:17:17,055
I have fallen a long way.

740
01:17:18,734 --> 01:17:21,259
The moon sees nothing of this.

741
01:17:24,706 --> 01:17:28,437
And the message of the yew tree
is blackness--

742
01:17:31,346 --> 01:17:33,871
blackness and silence.

743
01:17:40,822 --> 01:17:43,313
I don't know what else to do.

744
01:17:48,563 --> 01:17:50,554
I can't

745
01:17:53,568 --> 01:17:57,026
I can't go back to her,
but I love her so much it's--

746
01:18:17,893 --> 01:18:20,487
Do you want another one?
Mm.

747
01:18:23,265 --> 01:18:25,290
Thank you.

748
01:18:50,692 --> 01:18:53,422
This one is extraordinary.

749
01:18:53,495 --> 01:18:58,023
And, uh, ''Lady Lazarus, ''
the one about the, uh--

750
01:18:58,100 --> 01:19:01,866
the failed suicides--
the despair,

751
01:19:01,937 --> 01:19:05,566
the overpowering sense of foreboding,
and yet without a trace...

752
01:19:05,640 --> 01:19:08,404
of anger or hysteria...

753
01:19:08,477 --> 01:19:11,412
or any appeal for sympathy.

754
01:19:12,414 --> 01:19:16,407
The-- The wealth of imagery.

755
01:19:18,019 --> 01:19:20,146
Such horrors,

756
01:19:20,222 --> 01:19:23,282
but expressed with, um--

757
01:19:24,726 --> 01:19:27,718
with a coolness,

758
01:19:27,796 --> 01:19:31,630
like a--
like a murderer's confession.

759
01:19:37,139 --> 01:19:39,130
So

760
01:19:39,207 --> 01:19:42,040
have you got a title
for your novel yet?

761
01:19:42,110 --> 01:19:45,602
The Bell Jar.
When's it coming out?

762
01:19:47,149 --> 01:19:49,083
The New Year.

763
01:19:49,151 --> 01:19:51,984
Are you gonna let me read it?

764
01:19:52,053 --> 01:19:54,988
It's a potboiler.

765
01:19:58,527 --> 01:20:01,121
Could you get me an ashtray?

766
01:20:01,196 --> 01:20:03,221
Sure.

767
01:20:03,298 --> 01:20:07,394
I didn't know you smoked.
I don't.

768
01:20:07,469 --> 01:20:09,937
But I'm starting.

769
01:20:10,005 --> 01:20:12,473
I'm thinking of trying
some new things.

770
01:20:12,541 --> 01:20:15,567
Really? Like what?

771
01:20:18,013 --> 01:20:20,243
I'm thinking of taking a lover.

772
01:20:20,315 --> 01:20:23,341
Oh, how glamorous.

773
01:20:23,418 --> 01:20:25,352
Who is he?

774
01:20:54,816 --> 01:20:59,014
Look, I know how you feel.

775
01:20:59,087 --> 01:21:02,853
No, you don't.
I do.

776
01:21:04,726 --> 01:21:06,717
We have-- We share in common a--

777
01:21:09,631 --> 01:21:12,361
I...

778
01:21:12,434 --> 01:21:17,064
I tried to-- I tried to--

779
01:21:20,408 --> 01:21:22,342
How?

780
01:21:24,079 --> 01:21:27,776
Uh, same as you. Sleeping pills.

781
01:21:29,184 --> 01:21:32,745
I, uh-- I took too many.

782
01:21:32,821 --> 01:21:35,415
Everybody does, don't they?

783
01:21:47,168 --> 01:21:52,037
Sometimes I feel like I'm not... solid.

784
01:21:54,643 --> 01:21:57,168
I'm hollow.

785
01:21:57,245 --> 01:21:59,236
There's...

786
01:22:00,916 --> 01:22:02,850
nothing behind my eyes.

787
01:22:02,918 --> 01:22:05,409
I'm a negative of a person.

788
01:22:10,325 --> 01:22:14,056
It's as if I never--

789
01:22:14,129 --> 01:22:16,757
I never thought anything.

790
01:22:17,866 --> 01:22:22,701
I never wrote... anything,
I never felt anything.

791
01:22:26,408 --> 01:22:29,343
All I want is blackness--

792
01:22:31,613 --> 01:22:34,673
blackness and silence.

793
01:22:40,455 --> 01:22:43,049
Look,

794
01:22:43,124 --> 01:22:45,718
one thing I do know about death...

795
01:22:45,794 --> 01:22:49,389
is it is not a--

796
01:22:49,464 --> 01:22:53,400
a reunion or a homecoming.

797
01:22:53,468 --> 01:22:57,268
There's-- There's no--

798
01:22:57,339 --> 01:23:00,831
Your life doesn't flash before you and
the missing piece of you clicks into place.

799
01:23:00,909 --> 01:23:04,675
It's just-- There's just fuck all.

800
01:23:04,746 --> 01:23:06,839
There's nothing.

801
01:23:09,150 --> 01:23:12,779
So what do you do when your life...

802
01:23:12,854 --> 01:23:16,085
gets as bad as it can...

803
01:23:16,157 --> 01:23:18,421
and just keeps getting worse?

804
01:23:19,527 --> 01:23:23,657
You just keep going.

805
01:23:26,501 --> 01:23:28,992
Look.

806
01:23:31,072 --> 01:23:33,063
Listen.

807
01:23:34,142 --> 01:23:37,441
You are so beautiful.

808
01:23:37,512 --> 01:23:40,640
And you've--you've
a wonderful mind.

809
01:23:42,450 --> 01:23:47,353
And you are a great--
a great poet.

810
01:23:49,891 --> 01:23:51,984
And you and Ted,

811
01:23:52,060 --> 01:23:54,858
you understand each other
in ways that--

812
01:23:54,929 --> 01:23:59,025
that other people
can only dream about.

813
01:23:59,100 --> 01:24:01,500
So, for God's sakes, don't throw
it all away just because--

814
01:24:01,569 --> 01:24:05,335
I don't want to hear her name.

815
01:24:05,407 --> 01:24:10,902
I was gonna say
just because of an affair.

816
01:25:11,906 --> 01:25:14,238
Are you all right? Come in.

817
01:25:19,581 --> 01:25:21,947
Sit here.

818
01:25:23,118 --> 01:25:26,952
I'm gonna die. I'm gonna die soon.
Who's gonna take care of my babies?

819
01:25:27,021 --> 01:25:29,489
Mrs. Hughes, I don't understand.
What do you mean, you're going to die?

820
01:25:29,557 --> 01:25:31,957
Are you ill?
Have you been ill or--

821
01:25:32,026 --> 01:25:35,325
No, I'm not ill.
I think I really
should call the doctor.

822
01:25:35,396 --> 01:25:39,332
No, no, don't call a doctor.

823
01:25:39,400 --> 01:25:44,463
Don't you know what they do?
They hook you up to the eastern grid
and fill you full of sparks.

824
01:25:44,539 --> 01:25:47,440
Yeah. I'm sorry.

825
01:25:47,509 --> 01:25:49,875
No, I'm sorry.

826
01:25:49,944 --> 01:25:52,105
I'm just so on edge, I--

827
01:25:54,716 --> 01:25:58,049
I'm just so on edge, I--

828
01:25:58,119 --> 01:26:03,580
Oh, God, it's all my fault,
it's all my fault, it's all my fault.

829
01:26:03,658 --> 01:26:06,149
All I could think about is
what would happen if...

830
01:26:06,227 --> 01:26:09,196
somebody took him away from me.

831
01:26:09,264 --> 01:26:12,427
You see, if you fear
something enough,

832
01:26:12,500 --> 01:26:15,094
you can make it happen.

833
01:26:15,170 --> 01:26:17,104
That woman,

834
01:26:17,172 --> 01:26:20,198
I conjured her.

835
01:26:20,275 --> 01:26:22,368
I invented her.
Do you understand?

836
01:26:22,443 --> 01:26:25,003
No, I'm sorry. I don't.

837
01:26:29,450 --> 01:26:33,819
It's just that I'm so tired,
I'm so tired, I'm--

838
01:26:36,291 --> 01:26:39,749
If I could just sleep a little bit,
just a little bit--

839
01:26:39,827 --> 01:26:42,728
I'm just so exhausted.

840
01:26:42,797 --> 01:26:47,097
Perhaps we could get someone
to look after your children.
Oh, my God! I left them upstairs!

841
01:26:47,168 --> 01:26:52,128
No, don't go. I'll go and check,
see if they're all right.
Would you like me to do that?

842
01:26:52,207 --> 01:26:54,937
You stay there.

843
01:26:55,009 --> 01:26:56,977
You're a very nice man.

844
01:26:57,045 --> 01:26:59,479
Mm, no.

845
01:26:59,547 --> 01:27:03,244
You remind me a little of my father.

846
01:27:44,626 --> 01:27:47,186
Yes, hello, Kate. It's Sylvia.

847
01:27:49,264 --> 01:27:51,289
I'm all right. I'm--

848
01:27:51,366 --> 01:27:55,325
I was wondering if I could
come round and see you.

849
01:28:00,441 --> 01:28:02,409
I see. Okay.

850
01:28:22,463 --> 01:28:25,261
Dr. Hawkins, it's Sylvia.

851
01:28:27,168 --> 01:28:31,298
I...

852
01:28:31,372 --> 01:28:34,864
I need help. I...

853
01:28:34,942 --> 01:28:38,275
I don't think I can...

854
01:28:38,346 --> 01:28:40,405
manage.

855
01:30:35,863 --> 01:30:39,765
You look... very nice.

856
01:30:41,436 --> 01:30:43,529
You'd better come in.

857
01:31:01,923 --> 01:31:04,118
Would you like a drink?

858
01:31:07,295 --> 01:31:09,229
Please.

859
01:31:19,740 --> 01:31:22,004
What do you want, Sylvia?

860
01:31:28,716 --> 01:31:31,082
I wanted to see you.

861
01:31:35,089 --> 01:31:37,819
I thought that you...

862
01:31:37,892 --> 01:31:40,156
might like to see us.

863
01:31:40,228 --> 01:31:42,526
I thought there was
something wrong.

864
01:31:45,199 --> 01:31:48,862
Alvarez said you tried
to make a pass at him.

865
01:31:51,739 --> 01:31:56,073
And I've been told
you've been taking pills.
No.

866
01:33:04,045 --> 01:33:07,173
God, I missed you.

867
01:33:08,516 --> 01:33:11,451
I almost went mad.

868
01:33:15,856 --> 01:33:18,381
We're not even two people.

869
01:33:21,495 --> 01:33:25,659
Even before we met,
we were just...

870
01:33:25,733 --> 01:33:28,998
these two halves...

871
01:33:29,070 --> 01:33:31,971
walking around with big...

872
01:33:32,039 --> 01:33:36,237
gaping holes in us
shaped like the other person.

873
01:33:37,912 --> 01:33:41,643
And then we found each other
and we were finally a whole.

874
01:33:46,988 --> 01:33:50,424
But then it's as if we couldn't
stand being happy,

875
01:33:50,491 --> 01:33:54,552
so we ripped-- we ripped
ourselves in half again.

876
01:34:05,606 --> 01:34:10,509
In the spring,
we should go back to Devon.

877
01:34:10,578 --> 01:34:15,242
We'll go back to Devon
and it'll just be us...

878
01:34:15,316 --> 01:34:18,649
and the children and our work.

879
01:34:21,255 --> 01:34:24,656
It'll be like this
whole thing never happened.

880
01:34:25,693 --> 01:34:30,255
And the summer and the fall
and this awful winter--

881
01:34:32,066 --> 01:34:36,002
it'll all fade by the time
the leaves come out.

882
01:34:38,205 --> 01:34:42,665
And it'll just seem like some nightmare
that was never real.

883
01:34:53,587 --> 01:34:56,556
You don't love her
like you love me.

884
01:34:59,493 --> 01:35:03,793
You'll never have with her
what you have with me.
You know that.

885
01:35:06,734 --> 01:35:09,100
I know.

886
01:35:12,106 --> 01:35:14,438
Leave her.

887
01:35:18,779 --> 01:35:20,974
I can't.

888
01:35:29,256 --> 01:35:31,247
She's pregnant.

889
01:36:23,677 --> 01:36:26,874
Oh. Everything all right?

890
01:36:28,849 --> 01:36:30,942
Do you have any stamps?

891
01:36:31,018 --> 01:36:35,148
It's silly, I know, but I've got, uh--

892
01:36:35,222 --> 01:36:38,851
I've gotta post some letters
to America tonight and I--

893
01:36:38,926 --> 01:36:41,121
airmail, and I don't have any stamps.

894
01:36:41,195 --> 01:36:44,255
Well, can't you post them
in the morning?

895
01:36:46,200 --> 01:36:52,002
No. No, I've got-- I've got
a nurse coming in the morning.
You see, there's a nurse coming.

896
01:36:52,072 --> 01:36:55,064
And, anyway, I won't
be here in the morning.

897
01:36:55,142 --> 01:36:58,339
Oh, I see.
Yes, I think I've got some.

898
01:37:04,552 --> 01:37:07,578
Here we are.
Thank you.

899
01:37:07,655 --> 01:37:10,522
Stamps. Thanks.

900
01:37:10,591 --> 01:37:12,616
Thank you.

901
01:37:12,693 --> 01:37:14,923
Well, good night.
Good night.

902
01:37:59,607 --> 01:38:01,905
Look, do you want me
to call someone?

903
01:38:04,879 --> 01:38:06,870
No.

904
01:38:07,882 --> 01:38:11,409
No, I was just having--

905
01:38:11,485 --> 01:38:15,819
I just had the most beautiful... dream.

906
01:39:13,080 --> 01:39:16,106
I love you, sweetheart.

907
01:40:10,571 --> 01:40:14,132
The box is locked.
It is dangerous.

908
01:40:14,208 --> 01:40:18,508
There are no windows,
so I can't see what is in there.

909
01:40:18,579 --> 01:40:21,605
There is only a little grid.

910
01:40:21,682 --> 01:40:24,344
No exit.

911
01:43:58,445 --> 01:44:08,445
Hearing impaired by --TDB--

